Bring a large pan of water to the boil for the pasta with @salt{0.5%tsp}. Trim the
@green beans{80%g} then chop in half. Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g}. Zest and
halve the @lemon{1/2}.

Pop the @cooked pulled chicken{240%g}, @soured cream{150%g}, half the
@grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}, the lemon zest, @green pesto{45%g} and
tomatoes into another large #saucepan{} with the @water{50%ml} and season with
@salt{} and @black pepper{}. Bring to a simmer over a medium-high heat then lower
the heat to medium and simmer for ~{5-6%minutes}, stirring occasionally.

Add the @fresh tagliatelle{1} and green beans to the boiling water and simmer until
cooked, ~{4%minutes}. Once cooked, drain well in a #colander{}.

Add the cooked pasta and green beans to the chicken mixture, taste and add more salt
and pepper if you like with a squeeze of lemon juice.

> Add a splash of water if the pasta looks a little dry.

Divide between plates and top with the remaining hard Italian cheese. Enjoy!